<title>ITALY: Olivetti statement due soon.</title>
<headline>Olivetti statement due soon.</headline>
<dateline>MILAN 1996-09-18</dateline>
<text>
<p>An emergency board meeting at Italian information technology group Ing. C. Olivetti &amp; C. SpA was drawing to a close and a statement was due to be issued shortly, a spokeswoman for the group said on Wednesday.</p>
<p>Market sources said before the board meeting began that Olivetti chief executive officer Francesco Caio was expected to stand down and be replaced by Roberto Colaninno, who is linked closely to former group chairman Carlo De Benedetti.</p>
<p>Colaninno is currently managing director of auto components firm Sogefi SpA, controlled by De Benedetti's industrial holding company CIR - Compagnie Industriale Riunite SpA.</p>
<p>Milan newsroom +392-66102321</p>
